    "text": "The average alleles per locus was 2.66, indicating low polymorphism. The polymorphic information content (PIC) of gSSRs was higher than eSSRs. Most polymorphic gSSRs were di- and tri-nucleotide repeats (52.4% and 38.1% of loci, respectively). Cluster analysis differentiated genotypes into nine subgroups, separating wild mung bean accessions from cultivated accessions.",
    "entities": [],
    "relations": []
  },
  {
    "text": "The predominant race was TJD. TJD was virulent against Pg1, Pg2, Pg3, Pg4, Pg8, Pg9, and Pg15. TJD accounted for 35.8% in 2018 and 37.8% in 2019. The sub-predominant races were TJN and TKN. TJN accounted for 30.2% in 2018 and 28.3% in 2019. TKN accounted for 20.8% in 2018 and 12.3% in 2019. All isolates were virulent to Pg1, Pg2, Pg3, and Pg4. All isolates were avirulent to Pg6 and Pg16.",
